{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895657908,"sessionID":"ses_2845f27a9ffe3yf2G6rkHTUn84","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba126d0001jiGZK1zYSRYxTh","messageID":"msg_d7ba1155b001ysugUz4LyrStPy","sessionID":"ses_2845f27a9ffe3yf2G6rkHTUn84","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_86f362cb00db43f4b0a3f763","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/router.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/router.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: router-api\n3: title: Router API\n4: slug: /api-reference/router\n5: sidebar_label: Router API\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Router API\n9: \n10: The Router API provides session management and request routing capabilities.\n11: \n12: ## Base URL\n13: \n14: ```\n15: http://router:8080/api/v1\n16: ```\n17: \n18: ## Authentication\n19: \n20: All endpoints require JWT authentication:\n21: \n22: ```http\n23: Authorization: Bearer <token>\n24: ```\n25: \n26: ## Endpoints\n27: \n28: ### Sessions\n29: \n30: #### Create Session\n31: \n32: Creates a new session and provisions a sandbox.\n33: \n34: **Endpoint:**\n35: \n36: ```http\n37: POST /sessions\n38: ```\n39: \n40: **Request:**\n41: \n42: ```json\n43: {\n44:   \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n45:   \"runtime\": \"python-3.11\",\n46:   \"resources\": {\n47:     \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n48:     \"memory\": \"256Mi\"\n49:   },\n50:   \"metadata\": {\n51:     \"user\": \"alice\",\n52:     \"project\": \"demo\"\n53:   }\n54: }\n55: ```\n56: \n57: **Response:**\n58: \n59: ```json\n60: {\n61:   \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n62:   \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-abc-456\",\n63:   \"status\": \"provisioning\",\n64:   \"endpoints\": [],\n65:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\",\n66:   \"expiresAt\": \"2026-04-11T16:30:00Z\"\n67: }\n68: ```\n69: \n70: **Status Codes:**\n71: \n72: - `201 Created` - Session created successfully\n73: - `400 Bad Request` - Invalid input\n74: - `409 Conflict` - Session already exists\n75: - `429 Too Many Requests` - Session limit reached\n76: \n77: #### Get Session\n78: \n79: Retrieves session information.\n80: \n81: **Endpoint:**\n82: \n83: ```http\n84: GET /sessions/{sessionId}\n85: ```\n86: \n87: **Response:**\n88: \n89: ```json\n90: {\n91:   \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n92:   \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-abc-456\",\n93:   \"status\": \"running\",\n94:   \"endpoints\": [\n95:     {\n96:       \"name\": \"http\",\n97:       \"url\": \"http://sandbox-abc-456.default.svc:8080\"\n98:     }\n99:   ],\n100:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\",\n101:   \"expiresAt\": \"2026-04-11T16:30:00Z\",\n102:   \"lastActivity\": \"2026-04-11T15:35:00Z\"\n103: }\n104: ```\n105: \n106: **Status Codes:**\n107: \n108: - `200 OK` - Success\n109: - `404 Not Found` - Session not found\n110: \n111: #### Delete Session\n112: \n113: Terminates a session and cleans up resources.\n114: \n115: **Endpoint:**\n116: \n117: ```http\n118: DELETE /sessions/{sessionId}\n119: ```\n120: \n121: **Response:**\n122: \n123: ```http\n124: HTTP/1.1 204 No Content\n125: ```\n126: \n127: **Status Codes:**\n128: \n129: - `204 No Content` - Session deleted successfully\n130: - `404 Not Found` - Session not found\n131: \n132: ### Proxy\n133: \n134: #### Proxy Request\n135: \n136: Forwards requests to the sandbox instance.\n137: \n138: **Endpoint:**\n139: \n140: ```http\n141: POST /proxy/{sandboxId}/*\n142: ```\n143: \n144: **Headers:**\n145: \n146: ```http\n147: X-Session-ID: session-123\n148: ```\n149: \n150: **Behavior:**\n151: \n152: 1. Extract session ID from header or path\n153: 2. Validate session exists and is active\n154: 3. Lookup sandbox endpoint from session store\n155: 4. Forward request to sandbox\n156: 5. Return sandbox response\n157: \n158: ### Health\n159: \n160: #### Health Check\n161: \n162: Liveness probe endpoint.\n163: \n164: **Endpoint:**\n165: \n166: ```http\n167: GET /healthz\n168: ```\n169: \n170: **Response:**\n171: \n172: ```json\n173: {\n174:   \"status\": \"healthy\",\n175:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n176: }\n177: ```\n178: \n179: #### Readiness Check\n180: \n181: Readiness probe endpoint.\n182: \n183: **Endpoint:**\n184: \n185: ```http\n186: GET /ready\n187: ```\n188: \n189: **Response:**\n190: \n191: ```json\n192: {\n193:   \"status\": \"ready\",\n194:   \"checks\": {\n195:     \"redis\": \"ok\",\n196:     \"workloadManager\": \"ok\"\n197:   }\n198: }\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ## Client Examples\n202: \n203: ### Python SDK\n204: \n205: ```python\n206: from agentcube import Client\n207: \n208: client = Client(base_url=\"http://router:8080\", token=\"your-token\")\n209: \n210: # Create session\n211: session = client.create_session(\n212:     session_id=\"session-123\",\n213:     runtime=\"python-3.11\",\n214:     resources={\n215:         \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n216:         \"memory\": \"256Mi\"\n217:     },\n218:     metadata={\n219:         \"user\": \"alice\",\n220:         \"project\": \"demo\"\n221:     }\n222: )\n223: \n224: print(f\"Session ID: {session.id}\")\n225: print(f\"Sandbox ID: {session.sandbox_id}\")\n226: print(f\"Status: {session.status}\")\n227: \n228: # Get session info\n229: session = client.get_session(\"session-123\")\n230: print(f\"Endpoints: {session.endpoints}\")\n231: \n232: # Delete session\n233: client.delete_session(\"session-123\")\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ### Go Client\n237: \n238: ```go\n239: import (\n240:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\"\n241:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/api/v1\"\n242: )\n243: \n244: client := clientgo.NewClient(\"http://router:8080\", \"your-token\")\n245: \n246: // Create session\n247: req := &apiv1.CreateSessionRequest{\n248:     SessionID: \"session-123\",\n249:     Runtime:   \"python-3.11\",\n250:     Resources: &apiv1.ResourceRequirements{\n251:         CPU:    \"100m\",\n252:         Memory: \"256Mi\",\n253:     },\n254: }\n255: \n256: resp, err := client.CreateSession(context.Background(), req)\n257: if err != nil {\n258:     log.Fatal(err)\n259: }\n260: \n261: fmt.Printf(\"Session ID: %s\\n\", resp.SessionID)\n262: fmt.Printf(\"Sandbox ID: %s\\n\", resp.SandboxID)\n263: \n264: // Get session\n265: session, err := client.GetSession(context.Background(), \"session-123\")\n266: \n267: // Delete session\n268: err = client.DeleteSession(context.Background(), \"session-123\")\n269: ```\n270: \n271: ### cURL Examples\n272: \n273: ```bash\n274: # Create session\n275: curl -X POST http://router:8080/api/v1/sessions \\\n276:   -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n277:   -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n278:   -d '{\n279:     \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n280:     \"runtime\": \"python-3.11\"\n281:   }'\n282: \n283: # Get session\n284: curl http://router:8080/api/v1/sessions/session-123 \\\n285:   -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\"\n286: \n287: # Delete session\n288: curl -X DELETE http://router:8080/api/v1/sessions/session-123 \\\n289:   -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\"\n290: ```\n291: \n292: ## Error Codes\n293: \n294: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n295: |------|-------------|-------------|\n296: | `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Session does not exist |\n297: | `SESSION_EXISTS` | 409 | Session already exists |\n298: | `SESSION_LIMIT_REACHED` | 429 | Maximum sessions per client exceeded |\n299: | `SANDBOX_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Sandbox not found |\n300: | `SANDBOX_NOT_READY` | 503 | Sandbox is not ready |\n301: | `INVALID_INPUT` | 400 | Invalid request parameters |\n302: | `UNAUTHORIZED` | 401 | Missing or invalid authentication |\n303: | `RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED` | 429 | Rate limit exceeded |\n304: \n305: ## Related Documents\n306: \n307: - [Workload Manager API](/api-reference/workload-manager)\n308: - [Store API](/api-reference/store)\n309: - [Authentication Guide](/advanced/authentication)\n\n(End of file - total 309 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: router-api\ntitle: Router API\nslug: /api-reference/router\nsidebar_label: Router API\n---\n\n# Router API\n\nThe Router API provides session management and request routing capabilities.\n\n## Base URL\n\n```\nhttp://router:8080/api/v1\n```\n\n## Authentication\n\nAll endpoints require JWT authentication:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/router.md","time":{"start":1775895657876,"end":1775895657907}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895657910,"sessionID":"ses_2845f27a9ffe3yf2G6rkHTUn84","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba12959001Yi7Sl2RF32JS7N","messageID":"msg_d7ba1155b001ysugUz4LyrStPy","sessionID":"ses_2845f27a9ffe3yf2G6rkHTUn84","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2502bd1e4b704aaa817b9be1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/workload-manager.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/workload-manager.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: workload-manager-api\n3: title: Workload Manager API\n4: slug: /api-reference/workload-manager\n5: sidebar_label: Workload Manager API\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Workload Manager API\n9: \n10: The Workload Manager API provides sandbox lifecycle management and resource orchestration.\n11: \n12: ## Base URL\n13: \n14: ```\n15: http://workload-manager:8081/api/v1\n16: ```\n17: \n18: ## Authentication\n19: \n20: Service-to-service communication requires authentication:\n21: \n22: ```http\n23: Authorization: Bearer <service_token>\n24: ```\n25: \n26: ## Endpoints\n27: \n28: ### Sandboxes\n29: \n30: #### Create Sandbox\n31: \n32: Creates a new sandbox instance.\n33: \n34: **Endpoint:**\n35: \n36: ```http\n37: POST /sandboxes\n38: ```\n39: \n40: **Request:**\n41: \n42: ```json\n43: {\n44:   \"name\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n45:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n46:   \"runtime\": \"python-3.11\",\n47:   \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n48:   \"resources\": {\n49:     \"requests\": {\n50:       \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n51:       \"memory\": \"256Mi\"\n52:     },\n53:     \"limits\": {\n54:       \"cpu\": \"500m\",\n55:       \"memory\": \"512Mi\"\n56:     }\n57:   }\n58: }\n59: ```\n60: \n61: **Response:**\n62: \n63: ```json\n64: {\n65:   \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n66:   \"name\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n67:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n68:   \"phase\": \"Pending\",\n69:   \"podName\": \"\",\n70:   \"endpoints\": [],\n71:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n72: }\n73: ```\n74: \n75: **Status Codes:**\n76: \n77: - `201 Created` - Sandbox created successfully\n78: - `400 Bad Request` - Invalid input\n79: - `409 Conflict` - Sandbox already exists\n80: \n81: #### Get Sandbox\n82: \n83: Retrieves sandbox information.\n84: \n85: **Endpoint:**\n86: \n87: ```http\n88: GET /sandboxes/{sandboxId}\n89: ```\n90: \n91: **Response:**\n92: \n93: ```json\n94: {\n95:   \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n96:   \"name\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n97:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n98:   \"phase\": \"Running\",\n99:   \"podName\": \"sandbox-abc-pod-xyz\",\n100:   \"podIP\": \"10.244.0.5\",\n101:   \"endpoints\": [\n102:     {\n103:       \"name\": \"http\",\n104:       \"port\": 8080,\n105:       \"url\": \"http://10.244.0.5:8080\"\n106:     }\n107:   ],\n108:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\",\n109:   \"lastActivity\": \"2026-04-11T15:35:00Z\"\n110: }\n111: ```\n112: \n113: **Status Codes:**\n114: \n115: - `200 OK` - Success\n116: - `404 Not Found` - Sandbox not found\n117: \n118: #### List Sandboxes\n119: \n120: Lists sandboxes with optional filtering.\n121: \n122: **Endpoint:**\n123: \n124: ```http\n125: GET /sandboxes?namespace=default&phase=Running\n126: ```\n127: \n128: **Query Parameters:**\n129: \n130: | Parameter | Type | Description |\n131: |-----------|------|-------------|\n132: | `namespace` | string | Filter by namespace |\n133: | `phase` | string | Filter by phase (Pending, Running, Failed) |\n134: | `sessionId` | string | Filter by session ID |\n135: | `limit` | integer | Maximum results (default: 100) |\n136: | `continue` | string | Pagination token |\n137: \n138: **Response:**\n139: \n140: ```json\n141: {\n142:   \"sandboxes\": [\n143:     {\n144:       \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n145:       \"name\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n146:       \"namespace\": \"default\",\n147:       \"phase\": \"Running\",\n148:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n149:     }\n150:   ],\n151:   \"continue\": \"eyJpZCI6InNhbmRib3gtYWJjIn0=\"\n152: }\n153: ```\n154: \n155: #### Delete Sandbox\n156: \n157: Deletes a sandbox and cleans up resources.\n158: \n159: **Endpoint:**\n160: \n161: ```http\n162: DELETE /sandboxes/{sandboxId}\n163: ```\n164: \n165: **Response:**\n166: \n167: ```http\n168: HTTP/1.1 204 No Content\n169: ```\n170: \n171: **Status Codes:**\n172: \n173: - `204 No Content` - Sandbox deleted successfully\n174: - `404 Not Found` - Sandbox not found\n175: \n176: ### AgentRuntimes\n177: \n178: #### Create AgentRuntime\n179: \n180: Creates an AgentRuntime resource.\n181: \n182: **Endpoint:**\n183: \n184: ```http\n185: POST /agentruntimes\n186: ```\n187: \n188: **Request:**\n189: \n190: ```json\n191: {\n192:   \"name\": \"python-3.11\",\n193:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n194:   \"spec\": {\n195:     \"image\": \"volcanosh/agentcube-python:3.11\",\n196:     \"resources\": {\n197:       \"requests\": {\n198:         \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n199:         \"memory\": \"128Mi\"\n200:       },\n201:       \"limits\": {\n202:         \"cpu\": \"500m\",\n203:         \"memory\": \"512Mi\"\n204:       }\n205:     },\n206:     \"env\": [\n207:       {\n208:         \"name\": \"PYTHONUNBUFFERED\",\n209:         \"value\": \"1\"\n210:       }\n211:     ],\n212:     \"ports\": [\n213:       {\n214:         \"name\": \"http\",\n215:         \"port\": 8080,\n216:         \"protocol\": \"TCP\"\n217:       }\n218:     ]\n219:   }\n220: }\n221: ```\n222: \n223: **Response:**\n224: \n225: ```json\n226: {\n227:   \"name\": \"python-3.11\",\n228:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n229:   \"phase\": \"Pending\",\n230:   \"endpoints\": [],\n231:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n232: }\n233: ```\n234: \n235: #### List AgentRuntimes\n236: \n237: Lists available AgentRuntimes.\n238: \n239: **Endpoint:**\n240: \n241: ```http\n242: GET /agentruntimes?namespace=default\n243: ```\n244: \n245: **Response:**\n246: \n247: ```json\n248: {\n249:   \"agentRuntimes\": [\n250:     {\n251:       \"name\": \"python-3.11\",\n252:       \"namespace\": \"default\",\n253:       \"image\": \"volcanosh/agentcube-python:3.11\",\n254:       \"phase\": \"Running\"\n255:     },\n256:     {\n257:       \"name\": \"nodejs-18\",\n258:       \"namespace\": \"default\",\n259:       \"image\": \"volcanosh/agentcube-nodejs:18\",\n260:       \"phase\": \"Running\"\n261:     }\n262:   ]\n263: }\n264: ```\n265: \n266: ### CodeInterpreters\n267: \n268: #### Create CodeInterpreter\n269: \n270: Creates a CodeInterpreter resource.\n271: \n272: **Endpoint:**\n273: \n274: ```http\n275: POST /codeinterpreters\n276: ```\n277: \n278: **Request:**\n279: \n280: ```json\n281: {\n282:   \"name\": \"ci-abc-123\",\n283:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n284:   \"spec\": {\n285:     \"runtime\": \"python-3.11\",\n286:     \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n287:     \"resources\": {\n288:       \"requests\": {\n289:         \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n290:         \"memory\": \"256Mi\"\n291:       },\n292:       \"limits\": {\n293:         \"cpu\": \"500m\",\n294:         \"memory\": \"512Mi\"\n295:       }\n296:     },\n297:     \"timeout\": \"300s\"\n298:   }\n299: }\n300: ```\n301: \n302: **Response:**\n303: \n304: ```json\n305: {\n306:   \"name\": \"ci-abc-123\",\n307:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n308:   \"phase\": \"Pending\",\n309:   \"podName\": \"\",\n310:   \"endpoints\": [],\n311:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n312: }\n313: ```\n314: \n315: ### Health\n316: \n317: #### Health Check\n318: \n319: **Endpoint:**\n320: \n321: ```http\n322: GET /healthz\n323: ```\n324: \n325: **Response:**\n326: \n327: ```json\n328: {\n329:   \"status\": \"healthy\",\n330:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n331: }\n332: ```\n333: \n334: #### Readiness Check\n335: \n336: **Endpoint:**\n337: \n338: ```http\n339: GET /ready\n340: ```\n341: \n342: **Response:**\n343: \n344: ```json\n345: {\n346:   \"status\": \"ready\",\n347:   \"checks\": {\n348:     \"kubernetes\": \"ok\",\n349:     \"store\": \"ok\"\n350:   }\n351: }\n352: ```\n353: \n354: ## Client Examples\n355: \n356: ### Python SDK\n357: \n358: ```python\n359: from agentcube import WorkloadClient\n360: \n361: client = WorkloadClient(\n362:     base_url=\"http://workload-manager:8081\",\n363:     token=\"service-token\"\n364: )\n365: \n366: # Create sandbox\n367: sandbox = client.create_sandbox(\n368:     name=\"sandbox-abc\",\n369:     namespace=\"default\",\n370:     runtime=\"python-3.11\",\n371:     session_id=\"session-123\",\n372:     resources={\n373:         \"requests\": {\n374:             \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n375:             \"memory\": \"256Mi\"\n376:         },\n377:         \"limits\": {\n378:             \"cpu\": \"500m\",\n379:             \"memory\": \"512Mi\"\n380:         }\n381:     }\n382: )\n383: \n384: print(f\"Sandbox ID: {sandbox.id}\")\n385: print(f\"Phase: {sandbox.phase}\")\n386: \n387: # Get sandbox\n388: sandbox = client.get_sandbox(\"sandbox-abc\")\n389: \n390: # List sandboxes\n391: sandboxes = client.list_sandboxes(namespace=\"default\")\n392: \n393: # Delete sandbox\n394: client.delete_sandbox(\"sandbox-abc\")\n395: ```\n396: \n397: ### Go Client\n398: \n399: ```go\n400: import (\n401:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\"\n402:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/api/v1\"\n403: )\n404: \n405: client := clientgo.NewWorkloadClient(\"http://workload-manager:8081\", \"service-token\")\n406: \n407: // Create sandbox\n408: req := &apiv1.CreateSandboxRequest{\n409:     Name:      \"sandbox-abc\",\n410:     Namespace: \"default\",\n411:     Runtime:   \"python-3.11\",\n412:     SessionID: \"session-123\",\n413: }\n414: \n415: resp, err := client.CreateSandbox(context.Background(), req)\n416: \n417: // Get sandbox\n418: sandbox, err := client.GetSandbox(context.Background(), \"sandbox-abc\")\n419: \n420: // List sandboxes\n421: list, err := client.ListSandboxes(context.Background(), &apiv1.ListOptions{\n422:     Namespace: \"default\",\n423:     Phase:     \"Running\",\n424: })\n425: \n426: // Delete sandbox\n427: err = client.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), \"sandbox-abc\")\n428: ```\n429: \n430: ## Error Codes\n431: \n432: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n433: |------|-------------|-------------|\n434: | `SANDBOX_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Sandbox does not exist |\n435: | `SANDBOX_EXISTS` | 409 | Sandbox already exists |\n436: | `INVALID_RUNTIME` | 400 | Invalid runtime type |\n437: | `VALIDATION_FAILED` | 422 | Sandbox validation failed |\n438: | `CREATE_TIMEOUT` | 504 | Sandbox creation timeout |\n439: | `RESOURCE_QUOTA_EXCEEDED` | 429 | Resource quota exceeded |\n440: | `INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES` | 503 | Insufficient cluster resources |\n441: | `K8S_API_FAILURE` | 500 | Kubernetes API error |\n442: \n443: ## Related Documents\n444: \n445: - [Router API](/api-reference/router)\n446: - [Store API](/api-reference/store)\n447: - [Sandbox Manager API](/api-reference/sandbox-manager)\n\n(End of file - total 447 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: workload-manager-api\ntitle: Workload Manager API\nslug: /api-reference/workload-manager\nsidebar_label: Workload Manager API\n---\n\n# Workload Manager API\n\nThe Workload Manager API provides sandbox lifecycle management and resource orchestration.\n\n## Base URL\n\n```\nhttp://workload-manager:8081/api/v1\n```\n\n## Authentication\n\nService-to-service communication requires authentication:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/workload-manager.md","time":{"start":1775895657880,"end":1775895657909}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895657912,"sessionID":"ses_2845f27a9ffe3yf2G6rkHTUn84","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba12e4e001FdTlFpR8ByjKas","messageID":"msg_d7ba1155b001ysugUz4LyrStPy","sessionID":"ses_2845f27a9ffe3yf2G6rkHTUn84","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d0275b608c3f4d149dcd161b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/store.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/store.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: store-api\n3: title: Store API\n4: slug: /api-reference/store\n5: sidebar_label: Store API\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Store API\n9: \n10: The Store API provides session state storage with Redis/Valkey backends.\n11: \n12: ## Package\n13: \n14: ```go\n15: import \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n16: ```\n17: \n18: ## Interface\n19: \n20: ```go\n21: type Store interface {\n22:     // Ping checks store connectivity\n23:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n24:     \n25:     // GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves sandbox by session ID\n26:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n27:     \n28:     // StoreSandbox persists new sandbox\n29:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n30:     \n31:     // UpdateSandbox updates existing sandbox\n32:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n33:     \n34:     // DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes sandbox\n35:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n36:     \n37:     // ListExpiredSandboxes returns sandboxes expired before time\n38:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n39:     \n40:     // ListInactiveSandboxes returns sandboxes inactive before time\n41:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n42:     \n43:     // UpdateSessionLastActivity updates last activity time\n44:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n45:     \n46:     // Close closes the store connection\n47:     Close() error\n48: }\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ## Data Structures\n52: \n53: ### SandboxInfo\n54: \n55: ```go\n56: type SandboxInfo struct {\n57:     // Kind is the type of resource\n58:     Kind string `json:\"kind\"`\n59:     \n60:     // SandboxID is the unique identifier for the sandbox\n61:     SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n62:     \n63:     // SandboxNamespace is the Kubernetes namespace\n64:     SandboxNamespace string `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n65:     \n66:     // Name is the human-readable name\n67:     Name string `json:\"name\"`\n68:     \n69:     // EntryPoints are the access endpoints\n70:     EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n71:     \n72:     // SessionID is the associated session identifier\n73:     SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n74:     \n75:     // CreatedAt is the creation timestamp\n76:     CreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n77:     \n78:     // ExpiresAt is the expiration timestamp\n79:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n80:     \n81:     // Status is the current state\n82:     Status string `json:\"status\"`\n83:     \n84:     // LastActivity is the last activity timestamp\n85:     LastActivity time.Time `json:\"lastActivity,omitempty\"`\n86: }\n87: ```\n88: \n89: ### SandboxEntryPoint\n90: \n91: ```go\n92: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n93:     // Path is the URL path\n94:     Path string `json:\"path\"`\n95:     \n96:     // Protocol is the protocol (http, https, ws, wss)\n97:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n98:     \n99:     // Endpoint is the full endpoint URL\n100:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n101: }\n102: ```\n103: \n104: ## Event Types\n105: \n106: ```go\n107: type Event struct {\n108:     Type  EventType\n109:     Key   string\n110:     Value []byte\n111: }\n112: \n113: type EventType string\n114: \n115: const (\n116:     EventSet    EventType = \"set\"\n117:     EventDelete EventType = \"delete\"\n118: )\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ## Factory\n122: \n123: ### Create Redis Store\n124: \n125: ```go\n126: func NewRedisStore(config RedisConfig) (Store, error)\n127: ```\n128: \n129: **Configuration:**\n130: \n131: ```go\n132: type RedisConfig struct {\n133:     // Addr is the Redis address\n134:     Addr string `json:\"addr\" yaml:\"addr\"`\n135:     \n136:     // Password is the Redis password\n137:     Password string `json:\"password\" yaml:\"password\"`\n138:     \n139:     // DB is the database number\n140:     DB int `json:\"db\" yaml:\"db\"`\n141: }\n142: ```\n143: \n144: ### Create Valkey Store\n145: \n146: ```go\n147: func NewValkeyStore(config ValkeyConfig) (Store, error)\n148: ```\n149: \n150: **Configuration:**\n151: \n152: ```go\n153: type ValkeyConfig struct {\n154:     // Addr is the Valkey address (comma-separated for cluster)\n155:     Addr string `json:\"addr\" yaml:\"addr\"`\n156:     \n157:     // Password is the Valkey password\n158:     Password string `json:\"password\" yaml:\"password\"`\n159:     \n160:     // DisableCache disables client-side caching\n161:     DisableCache bool `json:\"disableCache\" yaml:\"disableCache\"`\n162: }\n163: ```\n164: \n165: ## Usage Examples\n166: \n167: ### Basic Operations\n168: \n169: ```go\n170: import (\n171:     \"context\"\n172:     \"time\"\n173:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n174:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n175: )\n176: \n177: // Create store\n178: s, err := store.NewRedisStore(store.RedisConfig{\n179:     Addr:     \"localhost:6379\",\n180:     Password: \"secret\",\n181:     DB:       0,\n182: })\n183: if err != nil {\n184:     log.Fatal(err)\n185: }\n186: defer s.Close()\n187: \n188: // Check connectivity\n189: err = s.Ping(context.Background())\n190: if err != nil {\n191:     log.Fatal(err)\n192: }\n193: \n194: // Store sandbox\n195: sandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n196:     Kind:             \"sandbox\",\n197:     SandboxID:        \"sandbox-123\",\n198:     SandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n199:     Name:             \"test-sandbox\",\n200:     SessionID:        \"session-123\",\n201:     CreatedAt:        time.Now(),\n202:     ExpiresAt:        time.Now().Add(time.Hour),\n203:     Status:           \"running\",\n204:     EntryPoints:      []types.SandboxEntryPoint{},\n205: }\n206: \n207: err = s.StoreSandbox(context.Background(), sandbox)\n208: if err != nil {\n209:     log.Fatal(err)\n210: }\n211: \n212: // Get sandbox by session ID\n213: retrieved, err := s.GetSandboxBySessionID(context.Background(), \"session-123\")\n214: if err != nil {\n215:     log.Fatal(err)\n216: }\n217: \n218: // Update sandbox\n219: retrieved.Status = \"idle\"\n220: retrieved.LastActivity = time.Now()\n221: err = s.UpdateSandbox(context.Background(), retrieved)\n222: if err != nil {\n223:     log.Fatal(err)\n224: }\n225: \n226: // Update last activity\n227: err = s.UpdateSessionLastActivity(context.Background(), \"session-123\", time.Now())\n228: if err != nil {\n229:     log.Fatal(err)\n230: }\n231: \n232: // List expired sandboxes\n233: expired, err := s.ListExpiredSandboxes(context.Background(), time.Now(), 100)\n234: if err != nil {\n235:     log.Fatal(err)\n236: }\n237: \n238: // List inactive sandboxes\n239: inactive, err := s.ListInactiveSandboxes(context.Background(), time.Now().Add(-5*time.Minute), 100)\n240: if err != nil {\n241:     log.Fatal(err)\n242: }\n243: \n244: // Delete sandbox\n245: err = s.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(context.Background(), \"session-123\")\n246: if err != nil {\n247:     log.Fatal(err)\n248: }\n249: ```\n250: \n251: ### Watch for Changes\n252: \n253: ```go\n254: // Watch for key changes (implementation dependent)\n255: events, err := s.Watch(context.Background(), \"session:session-123\")\n256: if err != nil {\n257:     log.Fatal(err)\n258: }\n259: \n260: for event := range events {\n261:     switch event.Type {\n262:     case store.EventSet:\n263:         fmt.Printf(\"Session updated: %s\\n\", event.Key)\n264:     case store.EventDelete:\n265:         fmt.Printf(\"Session deleted: %s\\n\", event.Key)\n266:     }\n267: }\n268: ```\n269: \n270: ## Error Handling\n271: \n272: ```go\n273: import \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n274: \n275: // Check for specific errors\n276: err := s.StoreSandbox(ctx, info)\n277: if err != nil {\n278:     if errors.Is(err, store.ErrNotFound) {\n279:         // Handle not found\n280:     }\n281:     if errors.Is(err, store.ErrConnectionFailed) {\n282:         // Handle connection failure\n283:     }\n284:     if errors.Is(err, store.ErrSerialization) {\n285:         // Handle serialization error\n286:     }\n287:     if errors.Is(err, store.ErrTransactionFailed) {\n288:         // Handle transaction failure\n289:     }\n290: }\n291: ```\n292: \n293: ## Redis Key Structure\n294: \n295: | Key Pattern | Type | Description |\n296: |-------------|------|-------------|\n297: | `sandbox:{session_id}` | Hash | Sandbox metadata |\n298: | `sandbox:expiry` | Sorted Set | Sandboxes sorted by expiration time |\n299: | `sandbox:last_activity` | Sorted Set | Sandboxes sorted by last activity |\n300: \n301: ## Configuration\n302: \n303: ### Environment Variables\n304: \n305: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n306: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n307: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Store backend (redis/valkey) |\n308: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes* | - | Redis address |\n309: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | No | - | Redis password |\n310: | `REDIS_DB` | No | `0` | Redis database number |\n311: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes* | - | Valkey address |\n312: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | No | - | Valkey password |\n313: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Disable client-side caching |\n314: \n315: \\* Required based on `STORE_TYPE`\n316: \n317: ## Related Documents\n318: \n319: - [Router API](/api-reference/router)\n320: - [Workload Manager API](/api-reference/workload-manager)\n321: - [Architecture Overview](/architecture/overview)\n\n(End of file - total 321 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: store-api\ntitle: Store API\nslug: /api-reference/store\nsidebar_label: Store API\n---\n\n# Store API\n\nThe Store API provides session state storage with Redis/Valkey backends.\n\n## Package\n\n```go\nimport \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n```\n\n## Interface\n\n```go","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/store.md","time":{"start":1775895657883,"end":1775895657911}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895657914,"sessionID":"ses_2845f27a9ffe3yf2G6rkHTUn84","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba134c7001vGbC8QkkSrAxCs","messageID":"msg_d7ba1155b001ysugUz4LyrStPy","sessionID":"ses_2845f27a9ffe3yf2G6rkHTUn84","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0a286bc5550642998d2253ce","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/sandbox-manager.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/sandbox-manager.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: sandbox-manager-api\n3: title: Sandbox Manager API\n4: slug: /api-reference/sandbox-manager\n5: sidebar_label: Sandbox Manager API\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Sandbox Manager API\n9: \n10: The Sandbox Manager API provides sandbox lifecycle management and warm pool operations.\n11: \n12: ## Package\n13: \n14: ```go\n15: import \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox\"\n16: ```\n17: \n18: ## Interface\n19: \n20: ```go\n21: type SandboxManager interface {\n22:     // Create creates a new sandbox\n23:     Create(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxInfo) error\n24:     \n25:     // Update updates an existing sandbox\n26:     Update(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxInfo) error\n27:     \n28:     // Delete deletes a sandbox\n29:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) error\n30:     \n31:     // Get gets a sandbox by name\n32:     Get(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n33:     \n34:     // List lists sandboxes by selector\n35:     List(ctx context.Context, selector labels.Selector) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n36:     \n37:     // WarmPool manages warm pool\n38:     WarmPool() WarmPoolManager\n39: }\n40: ```\n41: \n42: ## Warm Pool Manager\n43: \n44: ```go\n45: type WarmPoolManager interface {\n46:     // Precreate pre-creates sandboxes\n47:     Precreate(ctx context.Context, spec *SandboxSpec, count int) error\n48:     \n49:     // Acquire acquires a sandbox from warm pool\n50:     Acquire(ctx context.Context) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n51:     \n52:     // Refill refills warm pool\n53:     Refill(ctx context.Context, spec *SandboxSpec) error\n54:     \n55:     // Size returns current warm pool size\n56:     Size(ctx context.Context) (int, error)\n57: }\n58: ```\n59: \n60: ## Data Structures\n61: \n62: ### SandboxInfo\n63: \n64: ```go\n65: type SandboxInfo struct {\n66:     // Name is the sandbox name\n67:     Name string `json:\"name\"`\n68:     \n69:     // Namespace is the Kubernetes namespace\n70:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n71:     \n72:     // UID is the unique identifier\n73:     UID types.UID `json:\"uid\"`\n74:     \n75:     // RuntimeType is the runtime type\n76:     RuntimeType string `json:\"runtimeType\"`\n77:     \n78:     // SessionID is the associated session\n79:     SessionID string `json:\"sessionId,omitempty\"`\n80:     \n81:     // Status is the current status\n82:     Status SandboxStatus `json:\"status\"`\n83:     \n84:     // CreatedAt is the creation time\n85:     CreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n86:     \n87:     // ExpiresAt is the expiration time\n88:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"expiresAt,omitempty\"`\n89:     \n90:     // LastActivity is the last activity time\n91:     LastActivity time.Time `json:\"lastActivity,omitempty\"`\n92: }\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ### SandboxSpec\n96: \n97: ```go\n98: type SandboxSpec struct {\n99:     // Image is the container image\n100:     Image string `json:\"image\"`\n101:     \n102:     // Resources defines resource requirements\n103:     Resources v1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n104:     \n105:     // Environment variables\n106:     Env []v1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n107:     \n108:     // Ports to expose\n109:     Ports []v1.ContainerPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n110:     \n111:     // TTL is the time to live\n112:     TTL time.Duration `json:\"ttl,omitempty\"`\n113: }\n114: ```\n115: \n116: ### SandboxStatus\n117: \n118: ```go\n119: type SandboxStatus string\n120: \n121: const (\n122:     SandboxStatusPending    SandboxStatus = \"Pending\"\n123:     SandboxStatusCreating   SandboxStatus = \"Creating\"\n124:     SandboxStatusRunning    SandboxStatus = \"Running\"\n125:     SandboxStatusIdle       SandboxStatus = \"Idle\"\n126:     SandboxStatusTerminating SandboxStatus = \"Terminating\"\n127:     SandboxStatusTerminated SandboxStatus = \"Terminated\"\n128:     SandboxStatusFailed     SandboxStatus = \"Failed\"\n129: )\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ## Usage Examples\n133: \n134: ### Create Sandbox\n135: \n136: ```go\n137: import (\n138:     \"context\"\n139:     \"time\"\n140:     corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n141:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/resource\"\n142:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n143:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox\"\n144: )\n145: \n146: // Create manager\n147: mgr := sandbox.NewManager(kubeClient)\n148: \n149: // Create sandbox\n150: sb := &sandbox.SandboxInfo{\n151:     Name:        \"echo-agent-1\",\n152:     Namespace:   \"default\",\n153:     RuntimeType: \"python-3.11\",\n154:     SessionID:   \"session-123\",\n155:     Status:      sandbox.SandboxStatusPending,\n156:     CreatedAt:   time.Now(),\n157:     ExpiresAt:   time.Now().Add(time.Hour),\n158: }\n159: \n160: err := mgr.Create(context.Background(), sb)\n161: if err != nil {\n162:     log.Fatal(err)\n163: }\n164: ```\n165: \n166: ### Acquire from Warm Pool\n167: \n168: ```go\n169: // Acquire sandbox from warm pool\n170: sb, err := mgr.WarmPool().Acquire(context.Background())\n171: if err != nil {\n172:     log.Fatal(err)\n173: }\n174: \n175: fmt.Printf(\"Acquired sandbox: %s\\n\", sb.Name)\n176: ```\n177: \n178: ### Precreate Warm Pool\n179: \n180: ```go\n181: // Precreate sandboxes\n182: spec := &sandbox.SandboxSpec{\n183:     Image: \"volcanosh/echo-agent:latest\",\n184:     Resources: v1.ResourceRequirements{\n185:         Requests: v1.ResourceList{\n186:             v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"100m\"),\n187:             v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"128Mi\"),\n188:         },\n189:         Limits: v1.ResourceList{\n190:             v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"500m\"),\n191:             v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"512Mi\"),\n192:         },\n193:     },\n194: }\n195: \n196: err := mgr.WarmPool().Precreate(context.Background(), spec, 10)\n197: if err != nil {\n198:     log.Fatal(err)\n199: }\n200: \n201: // Refill warm pool when low\n202: err = mgr.WarmPool().Refill(context.Background(), spec)\n203: if err != nil {\n204:     log.Fatal(err)\n205: }\n206: \n207: // Check warm pool size\n208: size, err := mgr.WarmPool().Size(context.Background())\n209: if err != nil {\n210:     log.Fatal(err)\n211: }\n212: \n213: fmt.Printf(\"Warm pool size: %d\\n\", size)\n214: ```\n215: \n216: ### List Sandboxes\n217: \n218: ```go\n219: import metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n220: \n221: // List all sandboxes\n222: list, err := mgr.List(context.Background(), labels.Everything())\n223: if err != nil {\n224:     log.Fatal(err)\n225: }\n226: \n227: for _, sb := range list {\n228:     fmt.Printf(\"Sandbox: %s/%s - %s\\n\", sb.Namespace, sb.Name, sb.Status)\n229: }\n230: \n231: // List sandboxes by label\n232: selector, err := metav1.ParseSelector(\"runtime-type=python-3.11\")\n233: if err != nil {\n234:     log.Fatal(err)\n235: }\n236: \n237: list, err = mgr.List(context.Background(), selector)\n238: if err != nil {\n239:     log.Fatal(err)\n240: }\n241: ```\n242: \n243: ### Update Sandbox\n244: \n245: ```go\n246: // Get sandbox\n247: sb, err := mgr.Get(context.Background(), \"echo-agent-1\", \"default\")\n248: if err != nil {\n249:     log.Fatal(err)\n250: }\n251: \n252: // Update status\n253: sb.Status = sandbox.SandboxStatusRunning\n254: sb.LastActivity = time.Now()\n255: \n256: err = mgr.Update(context.Background(), sb)\n257: if err != nil {\n258:     log.Fatal(err)\n259: }\n260: ```\n261: \n262: ### Delete Sandbox\n263: \n264: ```go\n265: err := mgr.Delete(context.Background(), \"echo-agent-1\", \"default\")\n266: if err != nil {\n267:     log.Fatal(err)\n268: }\n269: ```\n270: \n271: ## Error Handling\n272: \n273: ```go\n274: import \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox\"\n275: \n276: err := mgr.Create(ctx, sb)\n277: if err != nil {\n278:     if errors.Is(err, sandbox.ErrSandboxNotFound) {\n279:         // Sandbox not found\n280:     }\n281:     if errors.Is(err, sandbox.ErrSandboxExists) {\n282:         // Sandbox already exists\n283:     }\n284:     if errors.Is(err, sandbox.ErrInvalidRuntime) {\n285:         // Invalid runtime type\n286:     }\n287:     if errors.Is(err, sandbox.ErrValidationFailed) {\n288:         // Validation failed\n289:     }\n290:     if errors.Is(err, sandbox.ErrCreateTimeout) {\n291:         // Creation timeout\n292:     }\n293: }\n294: ```\n295: \n296: ## Configuration\n297: \n298: ### Environment Variables\n299: \n300: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n301: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n302: | `SANDBOX_DEFAULT_NAMESPACE` | No | `default` | Default namespace for sandboxes |\n303: | `SANDBOX_WARM_POOL_SIZE` | No | `5` | Target warm pool size |\n304: | `SANDBOX_WARM_POOL_ENABLED` | No | `true` | Enable warm pool |\n305: | `SANDBOX_CREATION_TIMEOUT` | No | `300s` | Sandbox creation timeout |\n306: \n307: ## Related Documents\n308: \n309: - [Workload Manager API](/api-reference/workload-manager)\n310: - [Router API](/api-reference/router)\n311: - [Warm Pool Design](/advanced/warm-pool)\n\n(End of file - total 311 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: sandbox-manager-api\ntitle: Sandbox Manager API\nslug: /api-reference/sandbox-manager\nsidebar_label: Sandbox Manager API\n---\n\n# Sandbox Manager API\n\nThe Sandbox Manager API provides sandbox lifecycle management and warm pool operations.\n\n## Package\n\n```go\nimport \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox\"\n```\n\n## Interface\n\n```go","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/sandbox-manager.md","time":{"start":1775895657886,"end":1775895657913}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895657917,"sessionID":"ses_2845f27a9ffe3yf2G6rkHTUn84","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba1398f0014N1y6s8qnMZKF3","messageID":"msg_d7ba1155b001ysugUz4LyrStPy","sessionID":"ses_2845f27a9ffe3yf2G6rkHTUn84","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1f114702266c49de99b168e4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/picod.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/picod.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: picod-api\n3: title: PicoD API\n4: slug: /api-reference/picod\n5: sidebar_label: PicoD API\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # PicoD API\n9: \n10: PicoD is an in-sandbox daemon for command execution and process management.\n11: \n12: ## Package\n13: \n14: ```go\n15: import \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod\"\n16: ```\n17: \n18: ## Interface\n19: \n20: ```go\n21: type PicoD interface {\n22:     // Run executes a command and waits for completion\n23:     Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)\n24:     \n25:     // Start starts a command without waiting\n26:     Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)\n27:     \n28:     // RunWithStreaming executes a command with streaming output\n29:     RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error)\n30:     \n31:     // Kill terminates a running process\n32:     Kill(ctx context.Context, pid int) error\n33:     \n34:     // Health checks daemon health\n35:     Health(ctx context.Context) error\n36: }\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Data Structures\n40: \n41: ### Command\n42: \n43: ```go\n44: type Command struct {\n45:     // Path is the command to execute\n46:     Path string `json:\"path\"`\n47:     \n48:     // Args are the command arguments\n49:     Args []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n50:     \n51:     // Env are environment variables\n52:     Env []string `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n53:     \n54:     // Dir is the working directory\n55:     Dir string `json:\"dir,omitempty\"`\n56:     \n57:     // Stdin is the standard input\n58:     Stdin io.Reader `json:\"-\"`\n59: }\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### CommandResult\n63: \n64: ```go\n65: type CommandResult struct {\n66:     // ExitCode is the process exit code\n67:     ExitCode int `json:\"exitCode\"`\n68:     \n69:     // Stdout is the standard output\n70:     Stdout []byte `json:\"stdout,omitempty\"`\n71:     \n72:     // Stderr is the standard error\n73:     Stderr []byte `json:\"stderr,omitempty\"`\n74:     \n75:     // Duration is the execution duration\n76:     Duration time.Duration `json:\"duration\"`\n77:     \n78:     // OOMKilled indicates if process was OOM killed\n79:     OOMKilled bool `json:\"oomKilled\"`\n80:     \n81:     // Timeout indicates if execution timed out\n82:     Timeout bool `json:\"timeout\"`\n83: }\n84: ```\n85: \n86: ### Process\n87: \n88: ```go\n89: type Process struct {\n90:     // PID is the process ID\n91:     PID int `json:\"pid\"`\n92:     \n93:     // Command is the executed command\n94:     Command string `json:\"command\"`\n95:     \n96:     // StartTime is when the process started\n97:     StartTime time.Time `json:\"startTime\"`\n98:     \n99:     // Wait returns the exit status\n100:     Wait() (*CommandResult, error)\n101:     \n102:     // Signal sends a signal to the process\n103:     Signal(sig syscall.Signal) error\n104: }\n105: ```\n106: \n107: ### OutputHandler\n108: \n109: ```go\n110: type OutputHandler interface {\n111:     // OnStdout handles stdout chunk\n112:     OnStdout(chunk []byte)\n113:     \n114:     // OnStderr handles stderr chunk\n115:     OnStderr(chunk []byte)\n116:     \n117:     // OnComplete handles completion\n118:     OnComplete(result *CommandResult)\n119: }\n120: ```\n121: \n122: ### ResourceLimits\n123: \n124: ```go\n125: type ResourceLimits struct {\n126:     // Timeout is the execution timeout\n127:     Timeout time.Duration `json:\"timeout\"`\n128:     \n129:     // MaxMemory is the maximum memory in bytes\n130:     MaxMemory int64 `json:\"maxMemory\"`\n131:     \n132:     // MaxFileSize is the maximum file size in bytes\n133:     MaxFileSize int64 `json:\"maxFileSize\"`\n134:     \n135:     // MaxNetworkBytes is the maximum network I/O in bytes\n136:     MaxNetworkBytes int64 `json:\"maxNetworkBytes\"`\n137: }\n138: ```\n139: \n140: ## Factory\n141: \n142: ### Create PicoD\n143: \n144: ```go\n145: func New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) PicoD\n146: ```\n147: \n148: **Options:**\n149: \n150: ```go\n151: // WithWorkDir sets the working directory\n152: func WithWorkDir(dir string) Option\n153: \n154: // WithLimits sets resource limits\n155: func WithLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) Option\n156: \n157: // WithLogger sets the logger\n158: func WithLogger(logger *zap.Logger) Option\n159: \n160: // WithTimeout sets the default timeout\n161: func WithTimeout(timeout time.Duration) Option\n162: ```\n163: \n164: ## Usage Examples\n165: \n166: ### Basic Command Execution\n167: \n168: ```go\n169: import (\n170:     \"context\"\n171:     \"fmt\"\n172:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod\"\n173: )\n174: \n175: // Create PicoD\n176: p := picod.New(\"sandbox-123\",\n177:     picod.WithWorkDir(\"/workspace\"),\n178:     picod.WithTimeout(30*time.Second),\n179: )\n180: \n181: // Run command\n182: cmd := &picod.Command{\n183:     Path: \"python\",\n184:     Args: []string{\"-c\", \"print('hello')\"},\n185:     Env:  []string{\"PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1\"},\n186:     Dir:  \"/workspace\",\n187: }\n188: \n189: result, err := p.Run(context.Background(), cmd)\n190: if err != nil {\n191:     log.Fatal(err)\n192: }\n193: \n194: fmt.Printf(\"Exit code: %d\\n\", result.ExitCode)\n195: fmt.Printf(\"Output: %s\\n\", result.Stdout)\n196: fmt.Printf(\"Duration: %v\\n\", result.Duration)\n197: ```\n198: \n199: ### Streaming Output\n200: \n201: ```go\n202: type MyHandler struct {\n203:     stdout bytes.Buffer\n204:     stderr bytes.Buffer\n205: }\n206: \n207: func (h *MyHandler) OnStdout(chunk []byte) {\n208:     h.stdout.Write(chunk)\n209: }\n210: \n211: func (h *MyHandler) OnStderr(chunk []byte) {\n212:     h.stderr.Write(chunk)\n213: }\n214: \n215: func (h *MyHandler) OnComplete(result *picod.CommandResult) {\n216:     fmt.Printf(\"Completed with exit code: %d\\n\", result.ExitCode)\n217: }\n218: \n219: // Execute with streaming\n220: handler := &MyHandler{}\n221: result, err := p.RunWithStreaming(context.Background(), cmd, handler)\n222: if err != nil {\n223:     log.Fatal(err)\n224: }\n225: ```\n226: \n227: ### Long-Running Process\n228: \n229: ```go\n230: // Start process\n231: proc, err := p.Start(context.Background(), &picod.Command{\n232:     Path: \"python\",\n233:     Args: []string{\"server.py\"},\n234: })\n235: if err != nil {\n236:     log.Fatal(err)\n237: }\n238: \n239: fmt.Printf(\"Started process with PID: %d\\n\", proc.PID)\n240: \n241: // Wait for completion\n242: result, err := proc.Wait()\n243: if err != nil {\n244:     log.Fatal(err)\n245: }\n246: \n247: fmt.Printf(\"Process completed: %d\\n\", result.ExitCode)\n248: \n249: // Or send signal\n250: err = proc.Signal(syscall.SIGTERM)\n251: if err != nil {\n252:     log.Fatal(err)\n253: }\n254: ```\n255: \n256: ### Kill Process\n257: \n258: ```go\n259: // Kill a process by PID\n260: err := p.Kill(context.Background(), 12345)\n261: if err != nil {\n262:     log.Fatal(err)\n263: }\n264: ```\n265: \n266: ### Health Check\n267: \n268: ```go\n269: err := p.Health(context.Background())\n270: if err != nil {\n271:     log.Fatal(err)\n272: }\n273: \n274: fmt.Println(\"PicoD is healthy\")\n275: ```\n276: \n277: ## HTTP Endpoints\n278: \n279: PicoD daemon exposes HTTP endpoints for remote execution.\n280: \n281: ### POST /execute\n282: \n283: Execute a command.\n284: \n285: **Endpoint:**\n286: \n287: ```http\n288: POST /execute\n289: ```\n290: \n291: **Request:**\n292: \n293: ```json\n294: {\n295:   \"command\": \"python\",\n296:   \"args\": [\"-c\", \"print('hello')\"],\n297:   \"env\": {\"PYTHONUNBUFFERED\": \"1\"},\n298:   \"dir\": \"/workspace\",\n299:   \"timeout\": \"30s\"\n300: }\n301: ```\n302: \n303: **Response:**\n304: \n305: ```json\n306: {\n307:   \"exitCode\": 0,\n308:   \"stdout\": \"hello\\n\",\n309:   \"stderr\": \"\",\n310:   \"duration\": \"0.1s\",\n311:   \"oomKilled\": false,\n312:   \"timeout\": false\n313: }\n314: ```\n315: \n316: **Status Codes:**\n317: \n318: - `200 OK` - Command executed\n319: - `400 Bad Request` - Invalid request\n320: - `408 Timeout` - Execution timeout\n321: - `500 Internal Error` - Execution error\n322: \n323: ### POST /start\n324: \n325: Start a long-running process.\n326: \n327: **Endpoint:**\n328: \n329: ```http\n330: POST /start\n331: ```\n332: \n333: **Request:**\n334: \n335: ```json\n336: {\n337:   \"command\": \"python\",\n338:   \"args\": [\"server.py\"]\n339: }\n340: ```\n341: \n342: **Response:**\n343: \n344: ```json\n345: {\n346:   \"pid\": 12345,\n347:   \"command\": \"python server.py\",\n348:   \"startTime\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n349: }\n350: ```\n351: \n352: ### POST /kill\n353: \n354: Kill a process.\n355: \n356: **Endpoint:**\n357: \n358: ```http\n359: POST /kill\n360: ```\n361: \n362: **Request:**\n363: \n364: ```json\n365: {\n366:   \"pid\": 12345,\n367:   \"signal\": 15\n368: }\n369: ```\n370: \n371: **Response:**\n372: \n373: ```http\n374: HTTP/1.1 204 No Content\n375: ```\n376: \n377: ### GET /health\n378: \n379: Health check endpoint.\n380: \n381: **Endpoint:**\n382: \n383: ```http\n384: GET /health\n385: ```\n386: \n387: **Response:**\n388: \n389: ```json\n390: {\n391:   \"status\": \"healthy\",\n392:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\",\n393:   \"uptime\": \"1h30m\"\n394: }\n395: ```\n396: \n397: ### GET /processes\n398: \n399: List running processes.\n400: \n401: **Endpoint:**\n402: \n403: ```http\n404: GET /processes\n405: ```\n406: \n407: **Response:**\n408: \n409: ```json\n410: {\n411:   \"processes\": [\n412:     {\n413:       \"pid\": 12345,\n414:       \"command\": \"python server.py\",\n415:       \"startTime\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\",\n416:       \"memory\": 25600000\n417:     }\n418:   ]\n419: }\n420: ```\n421: \n422: ## Configuration\n423: \n424: ### Environment Variables\n425: \n426: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n427: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n428: | `PICOD_PORT` | No | `8083` | HTTP server port |\n429: | `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/workspace` | Default working directory |\n430: | `PICOD_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default execution timeout |\n431: | `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n432: | `PICOD_SANDBOX_ID` | Yes | - | Sandbox identifier |\n433: \n434: ## Error Handling\n435: \n436: ```go\n437: import \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod\"\n438: \n439: result, err := p.Run(ctx, cmd)\n440: if err != nil {\n441:     if errors.Is(err, picod.ErrTimeout) {\n442:         // Execution timed out\n443:     }\n444:     if errors.Is(err, picod.ErrOOMKilled) {\n445:         // Process was OOM killed\n446:     }\n447:     if errors.Is(err, picod.ErrNotFound) {\n448:         // Command not found\n449:     }\n450:     if errors.Is(err, picod.ErrPermission) {\n451:         // Permission denied\n452:     }\n453: }\n454: ```\n455: \n456: ## Related Documents\n457: \n458: - [Sandbox Manager API](/api-reference/sandbox-manager)\n459: - [Security Architecture](/architecture/security)\n460: - [Code Execution Guide](/advanced/code-execution)\n\n(End of file - total 460 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: picod-api\ntitle: PicoD API\nslug: /api-reference/picod\nsidebar_label: PicoD API\n---\n\n# PicoD API\n\nPicoD is an in-sandbox daemon for command execution and process management.\n\n## Package\n\n```go\nimport \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod\"\n```\n\n## Interface\n\n```go","truncate